x10.matrix.sparse

Class SparseCSC

  • x10.matrix.Matrix
    • x10.matrix.sparse.SparseCSC
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SymSparseCSC

    public class SparseCSC
extends Matrix
    This sparse matrix class uses CSC-LT format to store matrix nonzero elements. The underlying storage is defined in ComressArray.

    For testing purpose, the initialization of nonzero elements in the same column are generated one after another. The distance of the row index of two adjacent nonzero elements is determined randomly, while using the sparsity (nonzero density) to determine its average/mean.

        initRemoteCopyAtSource
        

        public x10.lang.Int initRemoteCopyAtSource(x10.lang.Int coloff,
                                  x10.lang.Int colcnt)
        

        Setup the remote copy of columns at the source sparse matrix.


         Before sparse matrix data can be transfered to a remote place,
the compressed storage must be modified to mark the starting element
of each column in the matrix.


         The start of each column is recorded by the fields "offset" in
Compress1D. To reduce the amount of data in
inter-place communication, only compressed data (CompressArray) is sent out.
Other fields in Compress2D and Compress1D are not transferred.


         The setup function will modify the index array to mark the start position
of the column, so that at the destination place, the target sparse matrix
can rebuild the start and length for compress columns.


         After the inter-place data transfer completes, finishRemoteCopyAtSource() must
be called to change index values back to original, otherwise computation
of index for nonzero elements will be ended in error.
        

        Parameters:
        coloff - the starting column in the source sparse matrix
        colcnt - number of columns to copy in the source sparse matrix
